Title: K\"ahler polarisation and Wick Quantisation of Hamiltonian systems
  subject to second class constraints
Authors: S. L. Lyakhovich, A. A. Sharapov
Comments: 8 pages, LaTeX
Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A17 (2002) 121-129
\\
  The necessary and sufficient conditions are established for the second-class
constraint surface to be (an almost) K\"ahler manifold. The deformation
quantisation for such systems is scetched resulting in the Wick-type symbols
for the respective Dirac brackets.
